WEBVTT

00:02.882 --> 00:03.687
Previously on Damages:

00:03.689 --> 00:06.743
I've been sitting at that
table all night hoping to get you alone.

00:06.811 --> 00:08.886
Opportunity doesn't always knock
twice.

00:08.954 --> 00:10.230
I'll take my chances.

00:10.231 --> 00:12.272
Why haven't you interviewed any
possible associates?

00:12.340 --> 00:14.476
There's only one
candidate who seems promising.

00:14.544 --> 00:16.047
Her name is Alex Benjamin.

00:16.049 --> 00:18.051
Maybe the world
needs people like Patty Hewes,

00:18.120 --> 00:20.259
but that doesn't mean that you
should go work for her.

00:20.327 --> 00:22.968
I don't understand. We never
invested with Louis Tobin.

00:23.035 --> 00:25.710
We gave our money to
Leverett and Leverett gave it to Tobin.

00:25.778 --> 00:26.814
We've lost everything.

00:26.815 --> 00:28.753
Did you know Dad was
gonna leave this behind?

00:28.821 --> 00:29.822
It explains where the money is.

00:29.823 --> 00:32.162
There's a name in there.
Stuart Zedeck.

00:32.229 --> 00:33.832
We'd like to start
making transactions.

00:33.833 --> 00:35.637
I'm afraid that's not
possible 'cause Mr. Zedeck

00:35.638 --> 00:37.408
is no longer comfortable with
the arrangement.

00:37.409 --> 00:39.867
Tell me the truth
about Danielle Marchetti.

00:39.934 --> 00:41.513
Louis had a child
with her.

00:41.514 --> 00:44.210
Yes. Do you know where
that child is now?

00:44.278 --> 00:46.163
The night he died,
I went to the apartment

00:46.164 --> 00:48.064
and I found that on the
coffee table near his body.

00:48.117 --> 00:50.478
Dr. Brandt, he made
the mix for Dad.

00:50.545 --> 00:52.882
Carol, I am really
sorry for your family.

00:55.152 --> 00:57.155
Ms. Marchetti?

00:59.460 --> 01:03.800
Roger wants to know what we think
of sending Megan to public school.

01:03.868 --> 01:06.572
No, that's not an
expense we want to cut.

01:06.640 --> 01:08.509
Well, how about the
lake house?

01:08.510 --> 01:12.180
You mean sell it?

01:12.248 --> 01:13.649
Tom makes a good living.

01:13.650 --> 01:16.120
I really don't see why we're
panicking.

01:16.188 --> 01:19.225
We're not panicking.
We're trying to be prudent.

01:19.292 --> 01:20.759
Are we?

01:20.760 --> 01:22.682
I have to say that
given the amount of financial

01:22.750 --> 01:24.946
assistance that you were
providing for both of your

01:25.014 --> 01:28.135
families, my advice would be to
make some changes.

01:28.203 --> 01:29.602
Well, I talked to my
mom.

01:29.603 --> 01:31.271
My folks are willing to cut
back.

01:31.272 --> 01:33.307
That's not gonna be
enough, all right.

01:33.374 --> 01:36.744
The Tobins have totally wiped
out our financial security.

01:36.812 --> 01:39.214
Not if you and Patty
recover more of the Tobin's funds.

01:39.281 --> 01:40.549
Don't count on that.

01:40.550 --> 01:42.184
What about Eric
Nichols?

01:42.185 --> 01:43.251
Deb.

01:43.252 --> 01:44.186
What?

01:44.187 --> 01:46.655
I don't know who
that is.

01:46.723 --> 01:48.958
Eric Nichols was our
financial advisor.

01:49.025 --> 01:51.061
He's the guy who got us all in
on the Ponzi scheme.

01:51.128 --> 01:53.697
He's a criminal.
He didn't do his due diligence.

01:53.764 --> 01:55.432
His kid goes to
Megan's school.

01:55.433 --> 01:56.933
Well, why can't we sue
him?

01:56.934 --> 01:57.934
Because...

01:57.935 --> 01:58.768
What?

01:58.769 --> 01:59.569
There's no evidence.

01:59.570 --> 02:00.937
Just stay clear of
him.

02:00.938 --> 02:04.808
There may be a way to litigate later
on, but for now just leave him alone.

02:04.876 --> 02:08.745
Going after Eric Nichols
is not the solution to our problem.

02:08.812 --> 02:11.548
We have to sell assets, we have
to cut costs.

02:11.615 --> 02:15.152
That's the only way we're gonna
save our family.

